text: Hickahala Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Hickahala is a name derived from the Choctaw language or Chickasaw language meaning "sweetgum tree". Variant names are "Hicaholahala", "Hicaholahia", "Hickahall", and "Hickahate". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of DeSoto County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Marshall County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Tate County, Mississippi
